"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DateFormatter in matplotlib expects the dates to be in the format that datestr2num returns, which is days since 0001-01-01 00:00:00 UTC, plus one. However, DateFormatter is being set to format the dates as '%d/%m/%Y'. The datestr2num function is being used correctly to convert the date strings to the correct format for matplotlib, but then the DateFormatter is being set to a different format. This will cause the dates on the x-axis to be displayed incorrectly.\",\n  \"patch\": \"13c13\\n<ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%d/%m/%Y\\\"))\\n---\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%m/%d/%Y\\\"))\\n\"\n}"